overview:
Muriel Lelandais is the CEO for Cellfish Canada, which develops the technological capital of Cellfish by ensuring sustainability of products, process efficiency and team expertise. She launched the Montreal office in June 2007, where she is based.

Muriel’s team consists mostly of developers and engineers who serve as Cellfish subsidiaries with technical solutions and infrastructures to support their products and business. She oversees the development, deployment, operation and maintenance of back-end solutions that require complex and innovative architecture, robust hosting and high performance. Additionally, her team develops user applications and front-end interfaces for the U.S. market.

degrees.institution: Ecole Supérieure de Commerce de Montpellier
